<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9800 MODEL - TESTING TRACTION ACTIVE LIGHT (ON
        INSTRUMENT PANEL)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING TRACTION ACTIVE LIGHT (ON INSTRUMENT PANEL)</title>
        <table id="t0403520" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Traction Active Light (On Instrument Panel)</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="s1t6">
                            <para>Perform
                                <hotlnk document="s04035v_25.xml" xrefid="t0403519">TESTING TRACTION CONTROL ON/OFF
                                    SWITCH
                                    <xref refid="t0403519"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                , before performing this test.
                                <emph type="bold">NOTE: Check Traction Active bulb for open filament before performing
                                    this test.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>The Traction Active Light and the ABS Warning Light share the same feed as the other
                                lights in the gauge cluster. If both lights do not work, check 10A fuse F9-D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Fuse OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect warning light from cab harness at connector (623). Key ON- at connector
                                (623) measure voltage to ground at circuit 94C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 94D/94C from fuse F6-C, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At warning light side of connector (623), measure resistance between the two black
                                wires with bulb installed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace the warning light/pigtail.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Connect light to harness at connector (623). Turn key ON- at connector (627), terminal
                                C2 (orange wire) measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Connect (627) to controller. Run
                                <hotlnk document="s04035v_7.xml" xrefid="t0403501">INITIAL START-UP TEST PROCEDURE
                                    <xref refid="t0403501"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                , and note if Traction Active Light illuminates for bulb test. If not replace the
                                controller.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 94BD/orange wire between connectors (623) and (627), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
